ast.comment: Kincob is a universal language syntax, you can use it in your Windows and your Windows Phone and do more with your device! http://os.basekit.com (This version needs Windows Phone 7.5)

This unit is here to run setup and configure for first time.
This big while is here to show the buffer after done a command and start to do a new command agian
echo is the text of Kincob's buffer.
This is Kincobs buffer, when buffer ask user a text and this command puts this text to a value (that name is Command) and we will use this value as users command
c2 is a back up of command for us.

Because Kincob has Tercore we made this unit to make it safe (how?) in Tercore we have a command that its "# /root/pass {text}" and using this command you can change your password but without this unit Kincob will save your password!

elseBody.text: This unit adds command to history directorys.

body.text: This unit deletes "sudo " from start of command, asks user the password and makes sudo := 1 if the password was correct and sudo := 2 if password is not correct.
